s in the trawlers, I could depend on thirty shillings a week, that was a good money. That was good money. That didna last so very long, when he went - deep sea, that was only four pound ten a month. But that was good money, if you got thirty shillings for
 a wage, or - a man could come in and give you thirty shillings or two pound you were a very lucky women.
