ork for other people myself - that - they used to come to me for advice. I've nursed the sick. I've been at births. During the war there I brought home a wee baby. Waited 'til doctor came. And I've done these sort of things. Because - when you're going an
d you see anybody in distress, I think - your own commonsense make you do the thing you ought to do.
