\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5585082 SO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 Well - I didn't need to be, becau
se what I - said was - law. When their father come home - if they done anything that was wrong he used to say, now it's your mother. Even up to the present day - if my children came in - and you know how they maybe would speak - that's your mother you're 
talking to. See? And I would just say the same, but nowadays - families don't seem to bother. I heard a wee girl telling her - father one day to go and get lost. I - I think that's - horrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid605028 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5585082 SO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid605028 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5585082 SO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 Sorry - pardon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid605028 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 How did you want them to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5585082 SO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 
Well just the same way, to respect you. To respect you and to let - and to understand that you were their mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid605028 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 When y
our children were small did you let them join in when grown ups were talking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5585082 SO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 
No, no. Oh no. If any grown up, just - like yourself coming in and speaking to me, if they were there - out they'd go, into the other room or out to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid605028 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 What did you bring them up to consider important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid5585082 SO  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13919541\charrsid12863516 
To consider important in life was to be respectable, bring their - themselves up to do to others as they'd like others to do to them. Keep their respectability and their independence. And when my children
 used - went out to get married I told them the same. You're leaving my house without debt, if you get into it it's your fault. Always be - try to be independent and that's what's the matter with me today. You just can't help that. It's there I think in o
l
der people. Now, you want to hear my girls when they're in here, they cry me for everything. They'll say, oh - you know mother if you weren't - if werenae so independent we could get this done and that done, see they'll come in and they'll say - I'm going
 
to do your windows. I say, no you're no doing the windows today. I feel if I see them doing it, I - why should I no try and do it. If I'm ill like. Because I've always one my own work, and I've always been able to do for myself. And I - as the doctor said
.
 He said that, he said - that's what the matter with your mother, been always active. Now that lady next door that's letting you in, this far back I've never known what it was to do that passage. She does it all the time. And I - I say to the girls you'd 
better bring in Mrs Angus something. You're mother's an awful woman, she's too independent, but you can't help that. Can't - and sometimes I feel in a way it's a good thing. They're running here and they're running therefore everything they can get.

